{"editorCode":"    \r\n\t  ;Picking Tiles\r\n\r\n;Alicia wants to cover her porch area with tiles. The porch is of rectangular shape of length 150 and width 270. \r\n;She found tiles of different shapes but she is confused.\r\n;Her friend, Liam, claims that different shapes correspond to different areas. Is he right?\r\n;Help Alicia to understand.\r\n\r\n;----------------        ;----------------\r\n;For further instructions click on the papyrus button.\r\n;----------------        \r\n\r\n;Tasks\r\n;------------\r\n;Task 1\r\n;................\r\nTo tiles1 :a :b :n\r\nstart\r\nrectangle :a :b\r\nblue\r\nfill1 :n :a :b\r\nprint 'area'\r\nend \r\n\r\n\r\nclean\r\ntiles1 150 270 30\r\n\r\n;Task 2\r\n;...............\r\nto tiles2 :a :b :n\r\nhome\r\nblack\r\nrectangle :a :b\r\nblue\r\nfill2 :n :a :b\r\nend \r\n\r\n\r\nclean\r\ntiles2 150 270 15\r\n\r\n;========================\r\n;========================\r\n\r\nTO rectangle :a :b \r\nblack\r\nrepeat 2 [fd :a rt 90 fd :b rt 90]\r\nend\r\n\r\nclean\r\nrectangle 20 30 \r\n;----------------\r\nto fill1 :n :a :b\r\nrepeat (:b)/(:n) [column1 :n :a]\r\nend\r\n\r\nclean\r\nfill1 4 \r\n;------------\r\nto column1 :n :a\r\nrepeat (:a)/(:n)[square1 :n  fd :n ]\r\nrt 90 fd :n rt 90 fd :a lt 180\r\nend\r\n\r\n\r\nclean\r\ncolumn1 \r\n;------------------\r\nto square1 :n\r\nrepeat 4[fd :n rt 90]\r\ndiag1 :n \r\nend\r\n\r\n\r\nclean\r\nsquare1\r\n;---------------------\r\nto diag1 :n\r\nlt 90 bk :n rt 45 fd :n*(sqrt(2)) rt 45 bk :n\r\nend\r\n\r\nclean\r\ndiag1 50\r\n;-------------\r\nto fill2 :n :a :b\r\nrepeat (:b)/(:n) [column2 :n :a]\r\nend\r\n\r\n;--------------------\r\nto column2 :n :a\r\nrepeat (:a)/(:n)[square2 :n  fd :n ]\r\nrt 90 fd :n rt 90 fd :a lt 180\r\nend\r\n\r\n;------------------\r\nto square2 :n \r\nrepeat 4[fd :n rt 90]\r\ndiag1 :n \r\ndiag2 :n\r\nend\r\n\r\n\r\n;-------------\r\nto diag2 :n \r\nrt 45 fd :n*(sqrt(2)) pu bk :n*(sqrt(2)) lt 45 pd\r\nend\r\n\r\n;--------------\r\nto start\r\npu setxy -130  -50 pd\r\nend\r\n\r\nstart\r\n\r\n\r\nto black \r\nsetpencolor [ 0 0 0]\r\nend\r\n\r\n\r\nto blue \r\nsetpencolor [ 0 0 255]\r\nend\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n\r\n","hiddenCode":[],"sceneCode":"","cameraPos":{"x":0,"y":1.2246467991473532e-14,"z":200},"character":"Bird","notes":"              Picking Tiles                                                *****************************\n\nTask 1\n..............................\n   Run the procedure \"tiles1\". Activate the variation tool (by clicking on the avatar's trace) and explore the role of its variables (a,b and n) by changing it with the tool's sliders. \n\n1. After running the procedure \"tiles1\", count:\n\n   •    How many tiles of square shape are there?\n   •    How many tiles of right-triangle shape are there?\n\nCalculate:\n\n   •    What is the area of the porch, considering as \nmeasurement unit the square tile? \n   •    What is the area of the porch, considering as \nmeasurement unit the triangular tile? \n\n2. Complete the procedure \"tiles1\" with the command \"print\" appropriately in order to print (at the Editor's output area) the area of the porch:\na)considering as measurement unit the square tile\nb)considering as measurement unit the triangular tile\n\n\nTask 2\n..............................\n1. Run the procedure \"tiles2\". Explore the role of the variables a, b and n by using the variation tool.\n Run the command «tiles2 150  270 30» and answer the questions:\n\n   •    What differences do you see between this procedure and the procedure \"tiles1\"?\n   •    How many tiles with the shape of the smallest isosceles triangle, cover the Alicia's porch?\n   •    How many different kind of tiles can you see? How many tiles are there in each case?\n \n2. Complete the procedure \"tiles2\" with the command \"print\" in order to print the area of the porch by using as measurement unit the tiles of different shapes (use one kind of shape at a time). How many different areas did you find?\n\n\n   •    Can you formulate a general conclusion on the area of any plane shape and on which two factors does it depend on?\n\n\n\t\t\t\t----------------\n\t\t\t\t       TIP\n\t\t\t\t---------------\nTask 1\n................................\n1. The number of the square tiles can be found by:\n\n              (:a/:n)*(:b/:n)\n\n   •    How many right triangular tiles form a square tile?\n\nTask 2\n.................................\n   •    How many of the smallest isosceles triangular tiles form a square tile?\n   •    How many of the right triangular tiles form a square tile?\n\n\n***In order to find the formula that would give you the number of the tiles on each case, find the relation between them and the area of Alicia's porch.\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","sliders":{},"objects":[]}